added.title: Extra, So Extra
added.description: Babs realizes Acme Loo's school paper has closed so she starts a new one with her pal Sweetie. But when Plucky starts a gossipy tabloid to compete against them, which paper will come out on top?

added.title: Tooney Ball Lights
added.description: Buster and Sweetie join the Tooney Ball team during Electives Week while Babs and Plucky tackle the basics in Anvils 101, leaving Hamton on a journey to fix his indecisiveness.

added.title: Hashtag #1 Fan
added.description: Panda gets kidnapped by a pair of deranged French foxes.

added.title: Snow Place Like Home
added.description: When the Bears realize whatever they build with snow comes to life they decide to build the biggest snow party of all time.

added.title: Fiesta Day
added.description: The Bears party it up with a living piñatas for Fiesta Day. Wanting the festivities to never end, Grizz wishes for it to be Fiesta Day everyday.

added.title: Baba Yaga House
added.description: Squatter Otter tries to win Panda's trust and convince the Bears to live in a mysterious house.

added.title: Bears in the Dark
added.description: The Bears search for their missing box in a dark and scary cave.

added.title: Big Trouble Little Babies
added.description: When they realize they're too small for the rides at an amusement park, the Bears use a magic potion to get bigger.

added.title: Triple T Tigers
added.description: The Bears meet three cool tiger brothers. Grizz wants to be just like the oldest Tiger, TK, but he may not be the best role model.

added.title: Panda's Family
added.description: While exploring a lantern festival, the Bears encounter Panda's long-lost family.

added.title: A Tale of Two Ice Bears
added.description: The Bears accidentally clone Ice Bear and Ice Bear has a hard time adjusting.

added.title: Unica
added.description: The Bears join forces with Unica, the ultimate forest protector.

added.title: Gumbearable
added.description: After accidentally swallowing a piece of gum Owen has to protect his friends by jumping into gum volcano.

added.title: Whack Mirror
added.description: Chef warns Beth and Cody making goofy faces into a mirror will cause them to get stuck that way. It turns out he was right, just not in the way any of them ever imagined.

added.title: Broken Back Kotter
added.description: Izzy nominates Chef for the Daycare Professional of the Year award and will do whatever it takes to see him win. As it turns out, it takes a lot.

added.title: Weekend at Buddy's
added.description: After Cody's best friend doll breaks on their watch, Owen and Beth put themselves in grave danger while trying to do the right thing.

added.title: MacArthur Park
added.description: After losing countless jobs because of the kids, MacArthur shows up at the school seeking revenge.

added.title: Last Mom Standing
added.description: When Chef's Mom and Leshawna's Grandmother drop their loved ones off at the same time, it kicks off a dangerous competition for who is the most caring mother-figure.

added.title: Carmageddon
added.description: Duncan is rattled when Chef, tired of having his car destroyed, buys a new one that is completely indestructible.

added.title: Sugar & Spice & Lightning & Frights
added.description: When two new kids show up at the daycare Duncan and Leshawna take issue with, not what makes them different, but what makes them similar to the newbies.

added.title: Breaking Bite
added.description: Beth becomes the big dog on campus after she bites Duncan, but being the big dog is a dangerous thing, especially when you didn't actually bite anybody!

added.title: I Dream of Meanie
added.description: When Cody keeps screaming in his sleep Gwen and Duncan take a trip into Cody's dreams to see what is scaring him.

added.title: The Filth
added.description: Ben is tasked with cleaning the Rust Bucket. But when he is tricked into letting the villainous and vile Fly Guys steal it, he must chase them down before they create an unstoppable maggot monster with sights firmly set on destroying Las Vegas.

added.title: Waterfilter
added.description: Ben, Gwen, and Max's trip to Niagara Falls is cut short by the horrid Hydromanders, creatures menacing them and their fellow tourists.

added.title: The Ring Leader
added.description: While winning big on a Sumo Slammers video game, Ben gets the idea to win a wrestling match for real until an intimidating wrestler named Iron Kyle decides to make it a true challenge.

added.title: Riding the Storm Out
added.description: Ben and Gwen's camping trip is interrupted by the emotionless Weatherheads (Gust-o, Hail-o, & Shock-o) but a malfunctioning Omnitrix firing out a mishmash of aliens may not be the forecast for success.

added.title: The Clocktopus
added.description: In a peaceful coastal town, Ben must not only face the archaic antagonist Steam Smythe and his latest creation, the Clocktopus, but also his deepest, darkest fear: Squids!

added.title: Take 10
added.description: While trying to film his own indie film, Ben accidentally allows the Bug Gang to go free and when he takes the fight to their hidden lair Ben has to take on their narcissistic leader, the Ant Queen.

added.title: Growing Pains
added.description: During a stop at the superstore Shoppe, Ben and Gwen are transformed into babies by nanny-gone-nuts Nanny Nightmare, who will stop at nothing to reshape the world in the image of her daycare.

added.title: Shhh!
added.description: While chilling at a monastery with a no-noise policy, Ben can't keep quiet and accidentally awakens a dangerous Dragon hidden in a secret chamber below the hallowed halls. A job that might be too much for even Diamondhead to handle.

added.title: Brief Career of Lucky Girl
added.description: When a wizard cos player gets his hands on a real, magical wand at Comic Con, Ben enlists Gwen to help stop Hex from retrieving it by tricking the wicked warlock into thinking she is a powerful magic-wielder in her own right: the one and only Lucky Girl!

added.title: Animo Farm
added.description: Ben stumbles into Dr. Animo's secret lab now ruled by his superior mutants, the Alphas, and must help the lesser animals escape while stuck as Stinkfly.

added.title: Tourist Trap
added.description: While messing with the World's Largest Rubberband Ball at a tourist trap, Ben accidently releases some mischievous electrical creatures.

added.title: Kevin 11
added.description: After a big argument with Max, Ben rebels by going out on his own in the Big Apple and makes friends with Kevin 11, who has plans for the Omnitrix.

added.title: The Alliance
added.description: As Fourarms, Ben works to thwart an armored truck robbery by a tough female gang leader named Joey, who delivers a disturbing message from Vilgax.

added.title: Last Laugh
added.description: Ben's fear of clowns emerges at an unfortunate time when our heroes stumble upon a wicked circus with a psychic vampire clown named Zomobozo.

added.title: Lucky Girl
added.description: Ben battles an evil sorcerer whose power whose emanates from mystic charms, one of which turns Gwen into her own superhero named Lucky Girl.

added.title: Buff's BFF
added.description: When Buff befriends Mr. Freeze's snowcrawler Snowy, the other Batwheels bristle at the thought of hanging out with a "bad guy…" so Buff sets out to change their minds.

added.title: Up in the Air
added.description: After he causes the Batwing to crash, Bam becomes obsessed with making it up to her during a high-stakes aerial mission against Penguin and his giant ducky blimp.

added.title: Race Track Race
added.description: The Looney Builders race against the clock to build Cecil Turtle a new racetrack. Daffy gets caught up in his own desire to race and changes part of the build.

added.title: Dino Fright
added.description: George P. Mandrake hires The Looney Builders to build a T. Rex fossil. It's Tweety's job to place the bones with his crane, but his fear of the big dino affects his ability to get the job done.

added.title: Thomas Blasts Off
added.description: It's rocket launch day and all the trains get to help deliver the big rocket parts, but when Thomas is assigned a tiny part, he puts it off to help the others with their more exciting parts, not realizing that his "small" task was just as important.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: License to Deliver
added.description: When Percy has to deliver a new light bulb to the lighthouse at night, Thomas suggests playing secret agents along the way to help Percy forget about his fear of the dark.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Rules of the Game
added.description: When Thomas builds an obstacle course for his friends, he gets upset when they won't play with it HIS way.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: A Quiet Delivery
added.description: Thomas volunteers to get a sleeping Annie and Clarabel across Sodor without waking them up, only to discover that it's going to be harder than he imagined.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Kana Goes Slow
added.description: When Kana's power goes out during a delivery run, Thomas teaches her that sometimes it's okay to go slow.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: That Ol' Time Rock Rolls!/Make Like a Banana and Split
added.description: When Big Old Boulder rolls down the hill towards the museum, Berta needs the Mechas help to keep it stable./It's Food Day in Pretty Big City, but the Mechas need to help when the banana atop the banana split statue is not split!

added.title: Magnet Mayhem/Stop That Train
added.description: The magnet crane at the construction site accidentally turns on, sucking up all the metal, including the Mecha Builders!/Roof is delivering eggs to Marwyn at the Train Station, that is, until the train pulls into the station and can't stop!

added.title: Unlock the Magic: The Beginning
added.description: The discovery of an ancient, lost gateway leads the Care Bears on a rescue mission in the Silver Lining, a realm of natural wonders and comical creatures in the clouds beyond the borders of Care-A-Lot. While there, new discoveries expand the mission, challenging Cheer, Grumpy, and the mission team to grow beyond their present abilities and help the denizens of the Silver Lining.

added.title: A Patch of Perturbed Petunias
added.description: Share fears she's losing her ability as a problem-solver and peacemaker when she can't calm a squabble between a group of Whiffles and a flower bed of Perturbed Petunias. Cheer discovers it's not Share's fault; the Petunias are being secretly manipulated by Bluster's rumor-mongering.

added.title: Nobody's Perfect
added.description: When Cheer makes some simple mistakes, she begins to lose confidence in her piloting skills and herself. The self-doubt becomes so severe, she decides to step away from her role as pilot of the Cloudseeker. But the Team needs her, the Whiffles need her, and she must regain her self-confidence so they can stop Bluster's latest nefarious scheme.

added.title: A Yoorg Awakening
added.description: Funshine's jokes unwittingly hurt the feelings of a strange Rock Giant. Disturbed from its slumber, the usually benign creature inadvertently creates havoc for the Whiffles until Funshine calms it by apologizing.

added.title: Rain, Rain Go Away
added.description: After Grumpy's anger sends his belly badge out of control with a thunderstorm that floods a newly-planted Whiffle meadow, he vows to never be grumpy again. Renaming himself "Mr. Happy," he drives everyone crazy with niceness. When the Whiffles desperately need his clouds to make rain and Mr. Happy can't deliver, Cheer and the team must get him back in touch with his inner grump.

added.title: Secret Origin of the Batwheels
added.description: When Batman, Robin, and Batgirl are all captured, the Batcomputer brings the Bat-Vehicles to life. Now the newly-minted Batwheels must defend the Batcave and face off with the Legion of Zoom… all without Batman's help!

added.title: Stop That Ducky!
added.description: After snagging an ultra-fuel-cell upgrade, Penguin's Ducky Boat suddenly becomes the fastest vehicle in Gotham. Confident leader Bam must rally the Batwheels to stop the turbo-Ducky!

added.title: Splash Zone
added.description: Mayor Foghorn Leghorn hires The Looney Builders to build a giant water slide for Looneyburg's waterpark. He keeps adding onto the design with the support of Bugs until problems arise.

added.title: Ice Creamed
added.description: It's Taz's birthday, so The Looney Builders build him a huge ice cream sundae. Porky worries about making a mistake and delays the build causing the ice cream to start to melt.

added.title: Bedtime Routine
added.description: Jessica wants to be a big kid and get ready for bed all on her own, but she can't remember everything in her routine.

added.title: Small Uncle's Big Bath
added.description: When Jessica discovers her favorite toy is dirty she volunteers to give him a bath.

added.title: The Big Kid Playground
added.description: Jessica goes in the big kid part of the playground for the first time, and befriends Stanleigh.

added.title: Grocery Store Friend
added.description: While helping Duane at the supermarket, Jessica meets a new friend and has trouble staying focused on her responsibilities.

added.title: Glow Toy
added.description: When Jessica can't get a new toy to work, she learns a new way to appreciate it.
